review:
I love this place. It's Genius! Making a meal out of a bunch of appetisers allows you to sample a bunch of different things rather than picking one dinner choice. With 3 portions per appetiser, it is perfect for ordering a bunch and sharing. 
My don't miss recommendations are the wonton soup, duck spring rolls, spicy chicken dumplings and fish and pepper gridled dumplings! Also great prices on wine by the glass and excellent cocktail; 
The service and atmosphere at this location is spot on. Very friendly staff and a great vibe going on. Perfect for a meal with a friend or an interesting convo starter for a date.

Delicious Indian food in Covent Garden! 
There are great Indian options in London, but this restaurant really serves up a modern flair to some traditional classics
// SERVICE // courteous and prompt
// WAIT // 10 minutes at 9 PM On the weekend
// FOOD //
     + roti: chewy with a good bite, similar to naan 
     + Chicken tikka: tart and delicious, chicken was soft. 
     + Chicken ruby: never have had this before but the chicken was very tender and the roti was perfect for dipping!

When dining at Chiltern Firehouse, make reservations in advance and tell them you'd like to sit by the chef's counter. It's quite the experience - watching the cooks prepare the food together like a well-oiled machine. From here, you get to witness everything from the meat grilling to the meticulous plating. I must also say that service here is on point. Anyone who has dined with me knows that I drink water like a race horse. Flagging down waiters for refills are thus usually a problem, but not at Chiltern.
// Crab Stuffed Donuts (£7) - 4 stars
One of Nuno Mendes' signature creations, this unique snack is what the restaurant is best known for. These slider-sized donuts are filled with crab and topped with coral dusting. A great balance of sweet and savory to start the meal off.
// Firehouse Caesar (£12) - 3 stars
What separates this dish out from all the other Caesar salads is the crispy chicken skin they include. Flavor-wise, I didn't think it was anything special though.
// Spiced Cornish Crab & Lobster Omelette (£26) - 4 stars
This is not your typical scrambled omelette. As seen in the picture, the ingredients actually sit on top of the eggs rather than being mixed in. The coral mayo helped pull all the components together, with the shiso leaves adding in a nice touch.
// Frozen Apple Panna Cotta (£9) - 5 stars
I debated for the longest time whether or not to order this dessert, but I'm sure glad I went for it. Such a beautifully plated finale. I especially enjoyed the herb granite, which was spectacular both visually and in taste.
